habitat_description: The San Simeon slender salamander occurs in the Santa Lucia Range in southwestern Monterey County and in northern San Luis Obispo County in central coastal California (Lannoo 2005; Green et al. 2013). They usually occupy localities in the mountains, but are also found near sea level in the northwestern limits of their distribution. According to Jockusch et al. (2001), this species occurs in both closed and open forest habitats where yellow pine is predominant. Individuals can be found near the Pacific Coast in the leaf litter in sycamore and laurel overstory; usually found in forest edge while absent from well-developed oak forest (Lannoo 2005).
